        "text": "Patterns are tools for sense-making, purpose driven design - the purpose being wholeness and enlivenment. Patterns allow us to semi-formalize and communicate both expert and tacit knowledge within specific domains of practice. They can be mined and applied at any level. It's more: patterns help us overcoming the very idea of vertical stratification of society (micro, meso, macro) because a patterns approach responds to and accomodates the pluralistic nature of the manyfold interconnections and feedback-loops (across levels) in complex social systems. \n"
