        "text": "Our \"domain of practice\" is commoning. The agents of commoning can be small groups, big p2pnetworks and whole societies. The level of complexity is different according to the agent, of course, so we will need different sets of patterns for different agencies. Such as there are different sets of patterns for setting up a room, for building a house and for constructing a city. Nonetheless: the ethics patterning is based upon and the purpose patterns are mined for remains the same: To foster commoning on the one hand and to work for systemic change towards a society that allows commoning to thrive and endure in the long term. Moreover; any pattern of commoning at onr scale (preliminarily called \"macropattern\") is closely connected to other patterns at other scales - they need one another. \nThis is why working on \"macropatterns\" is fully complementary to the Triad of Commoning. "
